# Error handling & async read UX

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`** (skeletons, motion, recovery copy), **`async-ui.mdc`** (pending vs fetching), **`accessibility.mdc`** (announcements), **`api-layer.mdc`** (mutation toasts), **`feature-state.mdc`** (derive one status union per surface).

Every **data-driven surface** (page, section, list, table, card region) must implement **four states**: **loading**, **empty**, **error**, and **success** (content ready). Derive a single **`status` union** per surface in hooks or `src/lib/<domain>/` — see **`feature-state.mdc`**. Motion and micro-feedback stay in `interaction-polish.mdc`.

## Core rule

**Never ship a silent blank UI.** Users must always see *something* intentional: skeleton, empty guidance, error recovery, or content.

## Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// Bad — blank screen; user cannot tell loading vs broken vs empty
if (!data) return null;

// Bad — conflates loading and empty
if (!data) return <p>No data</p>;

// Bad — error swallowed
const { data } = useItems();
return <ItemList items={data ?? []} />;
```

```tsx
// Good — explicit branches
const { data, isPending, isError, error, refetch, isFetching } = useItems();

if (isPending) return <ItemsSkeleton />;
if (isError) return <ItemsError error={error} onRetry={() => void refetch()} />;
if (!data?.length) return <ItemsEmpty onCreate={openCreate} />;

return (
  <>
    {isFetching && <RefreshingIndicator />}
    <ItemList items={data} />
  </>
);
```

Prefer a small colocated component (`ItemsSection.tsx`) when the branch logic grows — still **one explicit path per state**.

## State matrix

| State | When | UI |
| ----- | ---- | -- |
| **Loading** | Initial fetch (`isPending`) | Skeleton matching final layout — not a lone page spinner |
| **Error** | `isError` | What happened + retry (and support path if needed) |
| **Empty** | Success + zero items / null entity | What this is, why empty, primary next action |
| **Success** | Data present | Content; optional subtle `isFetching` for background refetch |

**Empty ≠ error ≠ loading.** Never use the same copy for all three.

## TanStack Query conventions

```tsx
const query = useCampaigns();

// Initial load
if (query.isPending) return <CampaignsSkeleton />;

// Hard failure (no cached data to show)
if (query.isError) {
  return (
    <QueryErrorState
      message="Couldn’t load campaigns."
      onRetry={() => void query.refetch()}
    />
  );
}

const campaigns = query.data ?? [];

if (campaigns.length === 0) {
  return <CampaignsEmpty onCreate={() => navigate("/campaigns/new")} />;
}

return <CampaignTable rows={campaigns} isRefreshing={query.isFetching} />;
```

- **`isPending`** — no data yet → skeleton.
- **`isError`** — show recovery; use `failureCount` / `error` for copy when useful.
- **`isFetching` + cached data** — keep content visible; inline refresh indicator (`async-ui.mdc`).
- **Do not** clear the list to `[]` on every refetch unless product requires it.

## Success feedback

| Context | Pattern |
| ------- | ------- |
| List / detail load | Render content — success is the default branch |
| Mutation save | Toast or inline “Saved” on the control (`interaction-polish.mdc` §4) |
| Background sync | “Syncing…” / “All changes saved” in editor toolbar (`forms-and-drafts.mdc`) |

## Errors: what to show

Every error state answers (`interaction-polish.mdc` §16):

1. **What happened?** — plain language, not status codes alone
2. **Why?** — when it helps (offline, permissions, validation)
3. **What now?** — retry, go back, edit input, contact support

```tsx
// Bad
<p>Error</p>

// Good
<Alert variant="destructive">
  <AlertTitle>Couldn’t load campaigns</AlertTitle>
  <AlertDescription>Check your connection and try again.</AlertDescription>
  <Button variant="outline" size="sm" onClick={onRetry}>Retry</Button>
</Alert>
```

API mutation errors: toast + rollback in query hooks (`api-layer.mdc`) — not silent `console.error`.

## Empty states

Never bare “No data”. Include (`interaction-polish.mdc` §15):

- What this section is for
- Why it might be empty (first time, filters, permissions)
- Primary action (create, clear filters, upgrade)

## Partial / multi-region pages

Do not gate the **entire page** on the slowest query (`interaction-polish.mdc` §11). Each region owns its own loading / empty / error / success.

```tsx
// Good — dashboard regions load independently
<PageShell>
  <CampaignsSummary />
  <RecentActivity />   {/* own skeleton / error / empty */}
  <BillingWidget />
</PageShell>
```

## Accessibility

- Loading regions: `aria-busy="true"` when appropriate (`accessibility.mdc`).
- Errors: visible text + retry; `role="alert"` for critical inline errors.
- Do not rely on color alone for error vs success.

## Checklist

- [ ] No `if (!data) return null` on user-facing data surfaces.
- [ ] Loading uses skeleton or structured placeholder — not an empty div.
- [ ] Empty state explains and offers a next step.
- [ ] Error state offers retry or clear recovery.
- [ ] Success branch renders real content; mutations acknowledge save/sync.
- [ ] Multi-query pages handle each region’s states independently.
